        "title": "Add channel turn delivery and control-lane diagnostics",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nThis PR adds a small, source-level Agentic Kernel spike for OpenClaw channel turns. The goal is not a rewrite: it makes Telegram/direct-message delivery and control-lane health observable and testable through existing runtime paths.\n\nKey pieces:\n- Adds turn event state modeling for received messages, turn lifecycle, delivery requirements, delivery sent/failed, and tool call/result causality.\n- Wires optional turn event recording into the existing channel turn kernel.\n- Adds control-lane priority helpers and tests for direct Telegram-like turns.\n- Adds gateway stability and channel-turn latency diagnostics for health/status/doctor surfaces.\n- Tightens stale task-flow audit handling for ended flows.\n- Keeps ordinary private Telegram DMs on the keyed lane while allowing only direct control-style DMs and authorized abort/stop messages to bypass the inbound debounce key.\n- Keeps the spike internals out of the public plugin SDK contract.\n\n## Verification\n\nPrepared and tested locally on the source branch:\n- targeted Vitest runtime suite: green\n- `pnpm tsgo:test`: green\n- `pnpm lint:extensions:no-plugin-sdk-internal`: green\n- `pnpm lint:plugins:plugin-sdk-subpaths-exported`: green\n- `git diff --check`: green\n- Strong secret-pattern scans over the PR file set and final local diff found no `ops_`, OpenAI-style API keys, GitHub tokens, private keys, or AWS access keys.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- **Behavior or issue addressed**: Telegram/direct-message control-lane and delivery diagnostics for Mira/OpenClaw must be observable from a real setup, with ordinary private Telegram DMs kept on a keyed lane and only direct control/abort messages allowed to bypass debounce.\n- **Real environment tested**: Sebastian's local Mira/OpenClaw runtime on the Mac-node setup, with Telegram connected, cron/tasks visible, and the real `mira-main` node path available. The evidence below is redacted and contains no message bodies, reminder titles, reminder bodies, or secret values.\n- **Exact steps or command run after this patch**:\n  - `python3 /Users/sebastian/.openclaw/workspaces/mira-main/scripts/mira_agent_os_fast_status.py`\n  - `python3 /Users/sebastian/.openclaw/workspaces/mira-main/scripts/mira_reminders_live_readiness.py --refresh`\n  - Targeted OpenClaw source verification: `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/channels/inbound-debounce-policy.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/control-lane-priority.test.ts src/channels/turn/turn-event-state.test.ts src/channels/turn/kernel.test.ts src/plugin-sdk/channel-inbound.test.ts src/plugins/contracts/plugin-sdk-subpaths.test.ts extensions/telegram/src/bot.create-telegram-bot.test.ts`, plus `pnpm tsgo:test` and the two plugin SDK lint gates.\n- **Evidence after fix**: Redacted terminal output from the real setup after the fix:\n\n```text\nmira_agent_os_fast_status.py\nok=true\ncontrol_lane_ok=true\nhealth.ok=true\nhealth.telegram_connected=true\nhealth.telegram_running=true\nhealth.event_loop_degraded=false\nhealth.event_loop_delay_p99_ms=22.6\ntasks.running=0\ntasks.queued=0\ncron.total=14\ncron.not_ok=[]\ncron.running=[]\nexternal_waiting=0\nelapsed_ms=2139\n\nmira_reminders_live_readiness.py --refresh\nok=true\nsource=mira_main_node_exec_smoke\nnode_exec_ok=true\nreminders_live_ok=true\nstatus=ok\nevidence=\"echo returned 'node_exec_ok'; remindctl status returned 'Reminders access: Full access'\"\nused_path=\"exec host=node node=jarvis-nextgen-node\"\noutput_policy=\"Redacted readiness only; no reminder titles, bodies, secrets, or raw private content.\"\n```\n\n- **Observed result after fix**: The real Mira runtime is reachable with Telegram connected, the control-lane health path reports ok, there is no task backlog, cron is healthy, and the real Mac-node execution path works. In source tests, the updated Telegram path now proves that ordinary private DMs remain keyed while direct control-style private DMs and authorized aborts get the intended priority behavior.\n- **What was not tested**: I did not run a maintainer-owned Mantis/Telegram Desktop live capture inside the upstream OpenClaw environment. The PR includes local real-runtime proof plus source-level tests; a maintainer can still request Mantis proof for an upstream-owned live Telegram Desktop demonstration.\n\n## Notes\n\nThis is intentionally update-safe/source-first work. It does not patch the installed OpenClaw `dist` runtime and does not add a second runtime or Telegram bridge.\n",
